The speakers of both the senate and national assembly have extended the debate on the constitutional amendment bill 2020 to next week automatically suspending the vote that members were expected to take at the end of the 2-day special sitting that was to end Thursday evening. the speakers Justin muturi and ken Lusaka argued that given the magnitude of the debate and interest that the amendment bill has attracted, it will be crucial to give nearly all members a chance to contribute before making. the ultimate decision on whether to support or reject the bill. and as Chris Thairu reports, members are still divided on the constitutionality of the bill.